<br>
I'm new to the server (only level 12), so if that changes how you view my response, well, I can't help that. Having read through many, many of the posts here on the forums, it seems to me that Shintou is one of the reasons I came to this server. I am a huge fan of RP (D&amp;D when I was very young, Whitewolf era since, and yes I have done Vampire LARPs), and although I have not had the pleasure of encountering Shintou in game, I think if all of us cared as much as he does, FV would be a better server overall.<br>
<br>
Ahem, that said, I don't think the issue of using shortcuts (e.g. omw, brb) is necessarily bad or contrary to RP, or even really the main concern here. In certain circumstances, typing everything out would actually be contrary to RP. For example, typing &quot;add&quot; mid-fight is analogous to me shouting &quot;behind you!&quot; and takes about as long. If I type &quot;behind you!&quot;, that takes longer than it would &quot;in character&quot; to shout &quot;behind you!&quot;, and would not maintain the RP feel of it. (If the person dies while you're giving the warning, it defeats the purpose of the warning in the first place.)<br>
<br>
I think the problem, in this case, is illustrated by an example given in another thread. I will present it as a hypothetical example since I can't remember enough particulars and see no need to involve specific names. An evil guild PLs an RL friend of the leader of the guild. The friend chooses to play a character that has a character concept contrary to the very nature of the guild doing the PLing. The only explanation given is &quot;We're RL friends and this is what friends do.&quot; Perhaps some psuedo-RP reasoning is given (i.e. both feel they are &quot;using&quot; the other, or some quick backstory is artificially invented that was never done in game, or something). <br>
<br>
Is it intrinsically wrong for a friend to PL another friend? In my opinion, no, not necessarily.<br>
<br>
Could it be considered &quot;unfair&quot; to people not as fortunate, who don't have high level friends on FV? Possibly. Irrelevant though.<br>
<br>
Is this contrary to the spirit of the server? Yes, definitely. The weird psuedo-explanation is actually worse because it suggests to others that RPing is &quot;Do whatever you want and explain it later&quot; instead of &quot;Figure out who your character is, and act how that character would act at all times.&quot;<br>
<br>
Can this eventually lead to a degradation of RP on the server? Likely so. This is because it gives us a bunch of high level people who, for whatever reason, have not experienced the character development inherent to levelling from 1-60. The fact that PLing is &quot;their thing&quot; leads me to think that they won't be much interested in developing their character after the fact. Having a bunch of high-level guilds where the people are into RP would be an awesome experience. Having a bunch of high-level guilds where the people all got PLed, well, that suggests the word &quot;uber&quot;, which we consider A Bad Thing for FV.<br>
<br>
Do I care about a degradation of RP on the server? Absolutely. RP is WHY I'm here. This server has been a dream for me since I starting playing EQ, and I have the same fears many others have that it might be lost or tainted, for the reasons already suggested.<br>
<br>
So I guess, if that's what Shintou was saying, then I agree with him totally. And to bring it to the original poster, that's why I care about PLing (on THIS server, on a normal blue server it would be totally, 100% acceptable in my eyes). Sorry for all the rambling, and it's great to be here on FV <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
