 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 7:25:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=229.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_bigsmile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: A Summary</span><hr size=1> I pretty much agree with you Kimaya...when in my earlier points i used the word &quot;Disdain&quot;...maybe too harsh....but i can say for sure, as like everyone else out there, i usually will group with those i enjoy.<br>
<br>
Lets say that i was a leader of a group in an area and after doing a /who, i saw 2 people i knew who were of the same class and around the same level that could be used in my group. I would ask the character i enjoyed playing with first if he would like to join us regardless to whether he was LFG or not and the other was...simply because i enjoyed his company. this is a fact. many of us are RP'ers here and enjoy the atmosphere of an RP'ing group. I have seen as of late many posts of people looking for groups and not being able to find one. This is not to suggest that this IS the reason why many have had a hard time finding groups...but if you fall into the non-RP department it could affect you.<br>
